Introduction to Digital Marketing in Tourism. PESO model as a framework applied in digital marketing activities. Content marketing for tourism and wellness brands ("owned" media). Mobile marketing, messengers and chantbota as effective channels for tourism and wellness communication. Online promotion and social media ("shared media"). User-generated content and virality in digital marketing. Influencer marketing and working with social crowds ("earned" media). SEO, SEM, SMM and Display advertising ("paid" media).Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course aims to develop students' understanding of the key concepts, principles and channels of digital marketing that will be relevant for professionals working in the spa and wellness industry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: * understands the role of digital marketing in service industries * knows the roles of stakeholders involved in various digital marketing processes * can apply the core digital marketing principles in practice and run digital marketing campaigns * can communicate to stakeholders the latest digital marketing strategies designed for the spa and wellness industries * can think critically and strengthen the decision-making and argumentation skills based on the proposed digital marketing ideas
